news.headline: Zscaler Slides Despite Strong Quarter
news.summary: Zscaler (NASDAQ:ZS) shares slid about 6% even though the company just posted a strong quarter and raised its outlook. Zscaler earned $0.96 per share on revenue of $788.1 million, beating forecasts.
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

Zscaler (NASDAQ:ZS) shares slid about 6% even though the company just posted a strong quarter and raised its outlook, a classic case of Wall Street shrugging at good news.

For the quarter ending Oct. 31, Zscaler earned $0.96 per share on revenue of $788.1 million, beating forecasts of $0.86 and $773.9 million. Sales jumped 26% from a year earlier, a clear sign that businesses are still investing in cybersecurity even as other tech spending slows.
